law.text:
As used in KRS 260.660 to 260.665, unless the context otherwise requires:
"Commission" means the Kentucky Milk Commission;
"Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Agriculture;
"Milk" means bovine lacteal secretion;
"Milk processor" means any person who purchases, receives, or handles greater than three million (3,000,000) pounds of milk per month; and
"Milk producer" means any person who produces milk for sale to milk processors.
